                  <summary change="#add-summary"> A copy of the <title>Shīrāznāmah</title> (Book of
                     Shiraz) a history of the city of Shiraz composed by late medieval-era author
                     and native Aḥmad ibn Abī al-Khayr Zarkūb Shīrāzī (ca. 1282–1387). It
                     records biographies of the rulers of <placeName>Fārs</placeName> province and
                     the famous spiritual leaders of the city up until the year <date
                        calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1343">744 AH (1343–44 CE)</date>.</summary>
